contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox Australian place | type = town | name = Warren | state = nsw | image = Warren NSW.JPG | caption = The post office and communications tower, Warren | latd =31 |latm =42 |lats = | longd =147 |longm =50 |longs = | pushpin_label_position = right | lga = [[Warren Shire Council]] | postcode = 2824 | est = | pop = 1,654 | pop_footnotes =<ref name=Census2006Y /> | elevation= 198 | maxtemp = 25.2 | mintemp = 10.5 | rainfall = 515.8 | stategov = [[Electoral district of Barwon|Barwon]] | fedgov = [[Division of Parkes|Parkes]] | dist1 = 536 | dir1 = WNW | location1= [[Sydney]] | dist2 = 128 | dir2 = NW | location2= [[Dubbo]] | dist3 = 85 | dir3 = W | location3= [[Gilgandra, New South Wales|Gilgandra]] | dist4 = 79 | dir4 = E | location4= [[Nyngan, New South Wales|Nyngan]] }} '''Warren''' is a town and the seat of a [[Local government in Australia|local government area]], [[Warren Shire Council|Warren Shire]], on the [[Macquarie River (New South Wales)|Macquarie River]] in central [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]. The town is located on the [[Oxley Highway]] 120 kilometres north west of [[Dubbo]]. It was laid out in the 1860s and incorporated as a municipality in 1895. The [[Warren railway line, New South Wales|railway]] reached the town in 1898. Warren is one of the main centres for the [[wool]] and [[cotton]] growing industries in New South Wales. At the 2006 [[Census in Australia|census]], Warren had a population of 1,654.<ref name=Census2006Y>{{Census 2006 AUS|id=UCL181600|name=Warren (Urban Centre/Locality) |accessdate=13 February 2010|quick=on}}</ref> ==Notable people from Warren== * [[Sharan Burrow]], former president of the [[Australian Education Union]], and current president of the [[Australian Council of Trade Unions|ACTU]].<ref name=ACTU>{{cite web | url = http://www.actu.asn.au/AboutACTU/actupresident/default.aspx | title= ACTU President - Australian Council of Trade Unions | accessdate = 2008-04-18 | publisher = [http://www.actu.asn.au/ Australian Council of Trade Unions}}]</ref> == References == {{Reflist}} ==External links== *[http://www.smh.com.au/news/new-south-wales/warren/2005/02/17/1108500200060.html SMH - Warren] *[http://www.warren.nsw.gov.au/ Warren Shire][http://www.macquariecaravanpark.com.au] [[Category:Towns in New South Wales]] {{NewSouthWales-geo-stub}}
